Consider the two graphs below:

Graph 1:
Number of Vertices: 4
Vertices: {A, B, C, D}
Number of Edges: 4
Edges: {(A,B), (B,C), (C,D), (A,D)}

Graph 2:
Number of Vertices: 4
Vertices: {W, X, Y, Z}
Number of Edges: 4
Edges: {(W,X), (X,Y), (Y,Z), (W,Z)}

Determine whether or not the two graphs are isomorphic. If they are isomorphic, provide an isomorphism between the two graphs. If they are not isomorphic, explain why not.
